Stem and seed bell pepper; finely dice pepper. Cut papaya into halves and discard seed; peel fruit and cut into 3/8-inch cubes. Combine bell pepper, papaya, chicken, cilantro, and capers. (If making ahead, cover and chill up to 4 hours.) Stir together lime peel, lime juice, and orange juice. Pour citrus juices over chicken mixture; stir to mix. Spoon chicken equally into melon halves; garnish with lime wedges. Add salt and pepper to taste.